 control.</para>
 </summary>
 <param name='sender'>The source of the event.</param>
 <param name='e'>A <see cref='System.Windows.Forms.DateTimeFormatQueryEventArgs'/> that contains the event data.</param>
 <remarks>
 <para>When you create a <see cref='System.Windows.Forms.DateTimeFormatQueryEventArgs'/> delegate, you identify the 
    method that will handle the event. To associate the event with your
    event handler, add an instance of the delegate to the event. The
    event handler is called whenever the event occurs, unless you remove the
    delegate. For more information about event handler delegates, see <see topic='cpconEventsDelegates'/>.</para>
